Deque (Double Ended Queue)
==========================

A Deque allows insertion & deletion from both ends.
It can be used as a stack (LIFO) or a queue (FIFO).
The Deque interface is part of the Java Collections Framework and provides methods for adding, removing, and examining elements at both ends of the deque.

Operations
----------
    addFirst()
    addLast()
    removeFirst()
    removeLast()
    peekFirst()
    peekLast()

Time Complexity
---------------
    All operations → O(1)

Types of Deque
----------------
1. Input Restricted Deque
    Insert from one side only
    Delete from both
2. Output Restricted Deque
    Delete from one side only
    Insert from both

Common Implementations
----------------------
    ArrayDeque → resizable array, no capacity restrictions, faster than LinkedList for deques
    LinkedList → implements Deque interface, allows null elements, slower than ArrayDeque for deques
